1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:06,077 --> 00:00:09,180
once you drop the ink, there's no telling
how it's going to spread, huh?

3
00:00:09,247 --> 00:00:10,515
But I guess

4
00:00:10,582 --> 00:00:14,352
<i>I was trying to control things</i>
<i>to make it turn out the way I want.</i>

5
00:00:14,919 --> 00:00:16,654
-Sora!
-Perhaps we were

6
00:00:16,721 --> 00:00:18,857
doing nothing but forcing our own feelings

7
00:00:18,923 --> 00:00:20,558
and expectations onto her.

8
00:00:20,625 --> 00:00:21,993
We'll try once more

9
00:00:23,261 --> 00:00:24,963
to see Nene eye to eye.

10
00:00:25,630 --> 00:00:26,831
<i>Tatsuki, do you have a kid?</i>

11
00:00:27,499 --> 00:00:28,366
Yeah.

12
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:30,735
You have to take good care of your family.

13
00:00:32,704 --> 00:00:33,805
Yeah.

14
00:00:51,222 --> 00:00:53,024
You were being followed?

15
00:00:54,092 --> 00:00:55,894
Although it could just be my imagination.

16
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:57,862
Wait, what did he look like?

17
00:00:57,929 --> 00:00:59,697
I didn't see his face.

18
00:00:59,764 --> 00:01:02,133
I was too scared to look back.

19
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:04,202
Have Tatsuki drop you off at home
for a while.

20
00:01:04,769 --> 00:01:07,505
He's tall, so he might at least
scare off creepy people.

21
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,874
I highly doubt that.

22
00:01:10,508 --> 00:01:11,709
Look at him.

23
00:01:13,278 --> 00:01:14,312
You're right.

24
00:01:21,352 --> 00:01:23,655
Tomoki Yanagisawa.

25
00:01:25,890 --> 00:01:28,159
Hey. Shi-chan, we should head out soon.

26
00:01:28,226 --> 00:01:29,594
Okay.

27
00:01:29,661 --> 00:01:31,296
All right, Ajicchan,

28
00:01:31,362 --> 00:01:32,664
-we'll be off.
-Have fun.

29
00:01:32,730 --> 00:01:34,599
-Bye.
-Bye.

30
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:36,734
-Mr. Tatsuki, we're heading out.
-Bye.

31
00:01:36,801 --> 00:01:38,002
Bye.

32
00:01:38,503 --> 00:01:40,004
Okay, listen up everyone.

33
00:01:40,972 --> 00:01:42,807
The time limit is 20 minutes.

34
00:01:42,874 --> 00:01:45,910
Let's find interesting materials
that are 500 yen or under!

35
00:01:48,446 --> 00:01:50,181
Soya, what do you mean by "materials"?

36
00:01:50,748 --> 00:01:52,951
Things like screws or lightbulbs.

37
00:01:53,518 --> 00:01:54,886
I'll look for a big screw.

38
00:01:56,487 --> 00:01:58,156
-A big one, huh?
-Will they have a guitar?

39
00:01:58,223 --> 00:01:59,791
It has to be under 500 yen, right?

40
00:01:59,857 --> 00:02:01,726
Yeah. I want materials for a necklace.

41
00:02:01,793 --> 00:02:03,628
-Let's go.
-Okay then, ready?

42
00:02:03,695 --> 00:02:04,529
Yup.

43
00:02:04,596 --> 00:02:06,064
Get set…

44
00:02:07,131 --> 00:02:08,132
Go!

45
00:02:28,419 --> 00:02:30,154
Is this your first time, Shi-chan?

46
00:02:31,923 --> 00:02:34,359
This project has got everyone
really hyped up.

47
00:02:34,425 --> 00:02:36,527
They're all taking this very seriously.

48
00:02:37,428 --> 00:02:40,698
There are lots of hidden gems here,
like retro machinery

49
00:02:40,765 --> 00:02:42,033
and vintage shirts.

50
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:43,067
That's nice.

51
00:02:43,134 --> 00:02:45,303
What should I choose?

52
00:02:45,370 --> 00:02:47,105
-I'm sure you'll find something.
-Soya.

53
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:52,510
Soya, this is 600 yen,
but can I still get it?

54
00:02:52,577 --> 00:02:57,015
But Uta, this is 100 yen over the budget,
so can you find something else?

55
00:02:57,081 --> 00:02:58,383
I want this one.

56
00:02:58,449 --> 00:03:01,786
Yeah, I'm sure. But there might be
something else that's just as nice

57
00:03:01,853 --> 00:03:02,920
so wanna go look together?

58
00:03:04,389 --> 00:03:05,256
-Okay.
-All right.

59
00:03:05,323 --> 00:03:07,659
Let's go.

60
00:03:08,559 --> 00:03:09,994
You might find something cute.

61
00:03:10,061 --> 00:03:11,562
-Yeah.
-Shi-chan.

62
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:14,499
Look at this. Isn't this cool?

63
00:03:14,565 --> 00:03:16,668
Wow, amazing.

64
00:03:16,734 --> 00:03:18,102
This is 500 yen?

65
00:03:18,169 --> 00:03:19,370
It's 3,500 yen.

66
00:03:20,204 --> 00:03:22,940
-Then you can't buy it. Go put it back.
-So stingy.

67
00:03:24,042 --> 00:03:26,010
-So stingy.
-Stingy?

68
00:03:27,145 --> 00:03:29,213
-Did you just call me stingy?
-Yup.

69
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,783
-This is nice.
-This is nice too.

70
00:03:31,849 --> 00:03:34,085
-What's this?
-I don't know.

71
00:03:34,152 --> 00:03:35,486
Um…

72
00:03:35,553 --> 00:03:36,921
what will you do with all of this?

73
00:03:38,122 --> 00:03:40,325
They'll be transformed into treasures.

74
00:03:40,391 --> 00:03:41,426
‎What?

75
00:03:43,127 --> 00:03:44,362
All right, everyone,

76
00:03:44,429 --> 00:03:47,165
let's use these things to create something
you like!

77
00:03:58,476 --> 00:03:59,944
Oh no.

78
00:04:00,011 --> 00:04:03,047
-I probably won't use any yarn.
-You don't need it?

79
00:04:06,551 --> 00:04:08,019
-Nice.
-It's a little too long.

80
00:04:08,086 --> 00:04:12,357
Yeah, maybe you should cut it a little.

81
00:04:12,423 --> 00:04:15,393
-There.
-What does this line represent?

82
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:16,694
The Keihin-Tohoku Line.

83
00:04:16,761 --> 00:04:18,196
I'm not talking about the train line.

84
00:04:22,066 --> 00:04:23,468
Gaku, what are you doing?

85
00:04:23,534 --> 00:04:27,305
This radio is broken
so I'm going to turn it into a robot.

86
00:04:27,372 --> 00:04:28,873
This will turn into a robot?

87
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:30,141
That's a great idea.

88
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:33,044
Shi-chan,
have you finished organizing that list?

89
00:04:33,611 --> 00:04:34,445
Yes.

90
00:04:34,512 --> 00:04:35,680
Thank you.

91
00:04:35,747 --> 00:04:37,949
Oh, I forgot. Mr. Tatsuki.

92
00:04:38,616 --> 00:04:39,984
Can I talk to you for a minute?

93
00:04:42,353 --> 00:04:43,388
YUKANAI MEMBERS LIST

94
00:04:43,454 --> 00:04:46,758
This student named Tomoki Yanagisawa
is someone I've yet to meet,

95
00:04:46,824 --> 00:04:49,527
but he's still a member here?

96
00:04:50,795 --> 00:04:53,331
He hasn't been coming for over six months.

97
00:04:53,931 --> 00:04:55,566
I wonder what the situation is.

98
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:58,069
Should we try contacting his family?

99
00:05:00,138 --> 00:05:03,641
His membership fee
is being paid every month.

100
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:07,044
Well, there are other students
who only come once in a while.

101
00:05:08,179 --> 00:05:09,313
How about I visit his house?

102
00:05:10,348 --> 00:05:12,116
There might be something going on

103
00:05:12,183 --> 00:05:15,486
that's preventing Tomoki
from leaving his house.

104
00:05:17,422 --> 00:05:19,257
I'll start by contacting his family.

105
00:05:24,495 --> 00:05:26,531
-Ms. Shizuku.
-Yes?

106
00:05:27,398 --> 00:05:28,833
There's something I want to do.

107
00:05:32,069 --> 00:05:32,904
TATSUKING

108
00:05:35,206 --> 00:05:36,507
DISTRICT 1
TATSUKING

109
00:05:36,574 --> 00:05:37,875
NO WEAPON

110
00:05:43,581 --> 00:05:44,982
You wanted to play a game?

111
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:46,517
Yeah.

112
00:05:48,986 --> 00:05:51,289
-Tatsuki, you're playing <i>Palxion</i>?
-Yeah.

113
00:05:51,355 --> 00:05:54,625
I played it a little while ago,
but I haven't played it recently.

114
00:05:55,626 --> 00:05:56,894
You have no weapon.

115
00:05:56,961 --> 00:05:58,830
You're unarmed.

116
00:05:58,896 --> 00:06:01,199
Leave me alone.
Being unarmed makes me cool.

117
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,334
Oh no!

118
00:06:03,401 --> 00:06:05,102
I got killed.

119
00:06:05,169 --> 00:06:06,671
You're so weak.

120
00:06:08,172 --> 00:06:09,907
I guess I need to pay money for weapons.

121
00:06:10,775 --> 00:06:12,076
Why are you playing this again?

122
00:06:13,444 --> 00:06:14,812
Because I'm searching for someone.

123
00:06:15,813 --> 00:06:16,647
Searching for someone?

124
00:06:16,714 --> 00:06:18,549
-In <i>Palxion</i>?
-Yeah.

125
00:06:19,784 --> 00:06:21,285
He hasn't been coming lately,

126
00:06:21,352 --> 00:06:23,488
but do you remember Tomoki Yanagisawa?

127
00:06:23,554 --> 00:06:24,555
Of course.

128
00:06:25,323 --> 00:06:27,124
You used to play with him.
What's his username?

129
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:28,826
What was it…?

130
00:06:29,627 --> 00:06:30,561
Was he good?

131
00:06:30,628 --> 00:06:32,763
Yeah, he was crazy good.

132
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,664
Oh, really?

133
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:37,335
He must be somewhere in this game.

134
00:06:38,269 --> 00:06:39,770
He's usually at District 18.

135
00:06:39,837 --> 00:06:41,806
-Really? I'll go there.
-Yeah.

136
00:06:41,873 --> 00:06:44,475
Wouldn't it be faster
to talk to him directly?

137
00:06:44,542 --> 00:06:46,310
I'm trying to do that right now.

138
00:06:50,281 --> 00:06:51,749
-Hey, I think that's Tomoki.
-Really?

139
00:06:51,816 --> 00:06:52,650
-Where?
-What?

140
00:06:52,717 --> 00:06:54,552
-Where is he?
-Give me that.

141
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,054
Let's see…

142
00:06:57,121 --> 00:06:58,689
Where did he go?

143
00:06:59,257 --> 00:07:00,858
-I just saw him.
-Really?

144
00:07:02,059 --> 00:07:04,028
‎TATSUKING

145
00:07:04,095 --> 00:07:04,962
Oh, there.

146
00:07:05,029 --> 00:07:06,697
-There! It's "haratomo999."
-What?

147
00:07:06,764 --> 00:07:08,232
-Is that it?
-Yeah.

148
00:07:08,299 --> 00:07:09,600
Try talking to him.

149
00:07:09,667 --> 00:07:12,103
I can't. He's on the enemy side.
We can only chat with allies.

150
00:07:12,169 --> 00:07:13,237
Oh, right.

151
00:07:15,072 --> 00:07:16,007
-Oh, crap.
-Watch out.

152
00:07:16,073 --> 00:07:17,208
-Let's hide for now.
-Yeah.

153
00:07:17,275 --> 00:07:19,277
If Tomoki is playing this game right now,

154
00:07:19,343 --> 00:07:21,479
that means he's home, right? Then I'll--

155
00:07:22,113 --> 00:07:22,947
It's a crucial moment.

156
00:07:23,648 --> 00:07:24,549
Come on…

157
00:07:26,918 --> 00:07:28,052
-Oh, no.
-Please

158
00:07:28,119 --> 00:07:30,121
don't kill us, Tomoki.

159
00:07:30,655 --> 00:07:31,489
Oh, crap.

160
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:36,794
This sucks.

161
00:07:39,697 --> 00:07:41,866
It's not my fault.

162
00:07:43,734 --> 00:07:46,404
Why did you log on to play that game?

163
00:07:46,470 --> 00:07:49,140
I thought we could talk more freely
within the game.

164
00:07:50,308 --> 00:07:52,843
What was the reason that brought

165
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:54,078
Tomoki to Yukanai?

166
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:58,149
He was bullied at his previous school.

167
00:07:58,649 --> 00:08:00,518
So he transferred schools.

168
00:08:01,018 --> 00:08:03,821
But he couldn't fit in
at his new school either.

169
00:08:05,122 --> 00:08:07,692
Bullying led to school refusal, huh.

170
00:08:08,292 --> 00:08:10,528
At first, he came to Yukanai
pretty regularly.

171
00:08:10,595 --> 00:08:12,129
But he gradually stopped coming.

172
00:08:13,664 --> 00:08:16,934
Then I wonder if he spends
all his time at home now.

173
00:08:18,235 --> 00:08:19,370
Most likely.

174
00:08:21,606 --> 00:08:22,773
Hello.

175
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,708
-Hello.
-Hello.

176
00:08:23,774 --> 00:08:25,209
I'm Tatsuki from Yukanai.

177
00:08:25,276 --> 00:08:27,078
I'm Aomine. Nice to meet you.

178
00:08:27,144 --> 00:08:28,713
Thank you for caring about my grandson.

179
00:08:28,779 --> 00:08:29,981
Sorry to come all of a sudden.

180
00:08:30,047 --> 00:08:32,650
No worries. The house is a bit of a mess,
but please come in.

181
00:08:33,284 --> 00:08:36,320
Is Tomoki's mother at work?

182
00:08:36,387 --> 00:08:37,321
Yes.

183
00:08:37,388 --> 00:08:40,658
She's actually
on a long-term business trip abroad.

184
00:08:40,725 --> 00:08:42,026
I see.

185
00:08:42,593 --> 00:08:44,362
Ever since it became just me and Tomoki,

186
00:08:44,428 --> 00:08:47,264
I've become unsure of how to handle him.

187
00:08:47,765 --> 00:08:49,734
He plays games in his room all day.

188
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,402
I see.

189
00:08:52,103 --> 00:08:54,705
I'm sorry for not contacting you
for so long.

190
00:08:54,772 --> 00:08:55,906
No problem at all.

191
00:08:55,973 --> 00:08:58,376
Whether they come or not
is entirely up to each child.

192
00:08:58,442 --> 00:08:59,944
So please don't worry.

193
00:09:01,045 --> 00:09:04,148
Is Tomoki
usually holed up in his room all day?

194
00:09:04,215 --> 00:09:07,251
No, he sometimes spends time out here too.

195
00:09:07,318 --> 00:09:09,220
I'm gonna kill you! Hey!

196
00:09:09,286 --> 00:09:10,888
Don't get away! Die!

197
00:09:12,323 --> 00:09:13,457
All right!

198
00:09:14,358 --> 00:09:16,694
That's usually how he is
when he's playing games.

199
00:09:16,761 --> 00:09:18,496
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay.

200
00:09:19,597 --> 00:09:21,298
There's no need to apologize.

201
00:09:23,334 --> 00:09:26,270
Games are sometimes
described as "life rafts."

202
00:09:26,337 --> 00:09:27,772
While playing to your heart's content,

203
00:09:27,838 --> 00:09:30,207
you may gradually
regain your sense of self.

204
00:09:31,008 --> 00:09:31,976
Is that so?

205
00:09:33,844 --> 00:09:35,012
Since I'm already here,

206
00:09:35,079 --> 00:09:37,314
would it be all right
if I spoke to him in person?

207
00:09:38,215 --> 00:09:39,750
-Oh… Mr. Tatsuki…
-Um…

208
00:09:39,817 --> 00:09:41,185
-Is it this way?
-Um…

209
00:09:41,252 --> 00:09:42,086
All right!

210
00:09:43,054 --> 00:09:44,088
Damn loser.

211
00:09:46,691 --> 00:09:47,825
Tomoki.

212
00:09:48,592 --> 00:09:50,795
It's Tatsuki from Yukanai.
It's been a while.

213
00:09:51,662 --> 00:09:53,497
I was wondering how you've been doing.

214
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:57,935
Just a while ago,

215
00:09:58,002 --> 00:10:00,037
I was playing <i>Palxion</i> too,

216
00:10:00,604 --> 00:10:02,406
but got killed by you in an instant.

217
00:10:03,674 --> 00:10:07,678
Tonetaku was helping me out,
but you're out of our league.

218
00:10:11,782 --> 00:10:13,150
Can I come inside?

219
00:10:13,718 --> 00:10:16,153
I want to watch you play the game.

220
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:17,321
You shouldn't…

221
00:10:20,324 --> 00:10:21,158
‎Sure.

222
00:10:33,871 --> 00:10:37,975
I'm going to play games with Tomoki now,
so you can go now.

223
00:10:38,042 --> 00:10:39,643
But Mr. Tatsuki…

224
00:10:44,181 --> 00:10:45,182
Man, it's a pigsty.

225
00:10:52,957 --> 00:10:53,924
These are so cool.

226
00:10:55,493 --> 00:10:57,328
-It's so lame.
-What is?

227
00:10:57,995 --> 00:10:59,530
The username, "Tatsuking."

228
00:11:01,699 --> 00:11:03,934
-Is that right?
-And you're so weak.

229
00:11:07,371 --> 00:11:11,542
I hadn't been playing that game lately.

230
00:11:11,609 --> 00:11:13,277
I'm learning from Tonetaku right now.

231
00:11:17,982 --> 00:11:18,983
You can have this.

232
00:11:21,185 --> 00:11:24,155
It's the <i>Palxion</i> sticker.
I won it at a convenience store.

233
00:11:24,789 --> 00:11:25,689
It's a rare item.

234
00:11:26,624 --> 00:11:28,692
-It's the Metallic Cannon.
-Yeah.

235
00:11:38,969 --> 00:11:42,439
Today we all went to a thrift shop

236
00:11:42,940 --> 00:11:44,575
and found some interesting things.

237
00:11:44,642 --> 00:11:47,912
Everyone used that as a base
to create all sorts of things.

238
00:11:49,079 --> 00:11:51,816
Some made dolls out of colorful socks,

239
00:11:52,383 --> 00:11:54,251
some made maracas by using

240
00:11:54,318 --> 00:11:56,687
a uniquely shaped cup and adzuki beans.

241
00:11:58,122 --> 00:11:59,156
You wanna try too?

242
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,759
-No, thanks.
-Really?

243
00:12:02,359 --> 00:12:05,129
But this room is filled with
all sorts of materials.

244
00:12:06,964 --> 00:12:07,898
It's all trash.

245
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,135
But it might transform
into something nice.

246
00:12:11,202 --> 00:12:12,136
No, thanks.

247
00:12:12,636 --> 00:12:13,470
-It's a hassle.
-Oh!

248
00:12:13,537 --> 00:12:15,973
This box has potential.

249
00:12:16,507 --> 00:12:17,908
This is nice too.

250
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:20,511
Stop touching my stuff.

251
00:12:20,578 --> 00:12:22,179
But it's trash, right?

252
00:12:22,746 --> 00:12:23,581
So who cares?

253
00:12:24,982 --> 00:12:26,016
This is nice too.

254
00:12:26,083 --> 00:12:29,220
I want to make something with this.
I wish I could…

255
00:12:30,487 --> 00:12:31,455
Fine.

256
00:13:37,688 --> 00:13:38,889
What's the matter?

257
00:13:42,026 --> 00:13:43,227
Why'd you come here?

258
00:13:45,496 --> 00:13:47,398
Because I haven't seen you in so long.

259
00:13:47,898 --> 00:13:49,733
So I was wondering how you're doing.

260
00:13:51,635 --> 00:13:53,671
I just wanted to see you, that's all.

261
00:13:57,007 --> 00:13:59,944
If you're doing well,
that's all that matters.

262
00:14:00,577 --> 00:14:02,079
Only come to Yukanai if you want to.

263
00:14:04,615 --> 00:14:06,283
Aren't you supposed to tell me to come?

264
00:14:08,152 --> 00:14:10,154
I used to be like that,

265
00:14:10,854 --> 00:14:12,523
but I screwed up because of it.

266
00:14:14,658 --> 00:14:15,559
How?

267
00:14:23,801 --> 00:14:26,370
There was a kid
who stopped going to school,

268
00:14:27,137 --> 00:14:29,707
<i>and I tried to drag him</i>
<i>out of his room by force.</i>

269
00:14:30,975 --> 00:14:32,009
<i>And it led</i>

270
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:35,012
<i>to results that could never be undone.</i>

271
00:14:38,816 --> 00:14:39,650
You were the worst.

272
00:14:41,685 --> 00:14:42,987
Yeah, definitely.

273
00:14:45,055 --> 00:14:47,524
I was truly the worst.

274
00:14:52,062 --> 00:14:53,564
That's why I never want you

275
00:14:54,465 --> 00:14:56,200
to push yourself too hard.

276
00:15:01,605 --> 00:15:03,640
But I have to end it.

277
00:15:06,677 --> 00:15:08,212
Since it'll be almost one year.

278
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,682
A year?

279
00:15:12,316 --> 00:15:14,418
Ever since I stopped going to school.

280
00:15:17,421 --> 00:15:18,455
I see.

281
00:15:21,892 --> 00:15:23,193
It looks like a face.

282
00:15:39,643 --> 00:15:40,844
I'm going to take this.

283
00:15:42,679 --> 00:15:43,680
What's that?

284
00:15:45,282 --> 00:15:46,550
A flower, I guess.

285
00:15:47,317 --> 00:15:48,185
I see.

286
00:15:48,685 --> 00:15:49,586
What's yours?

287
00:15:51,055 --> 00:15:53,824
I just slapped things together,
to make a car.

288
00:15:55,259 --> 00:15:56,794
You like cars?

289
00:16:04,535 --> 00:16:05,702
What's that?

290
00:16:07,471 --> 00:16:08,372
Dynamite.

291
00:16:19,183 --> 00:16:20,017
It's done.

292
00:16:22,386 --> 00:16:24,154
That looks cool.

293
00:16:26,123 --> 00:16:29,593
-Here, you can have it.
-What?

294
00:16:31,895 --> 00:16:33,330
Trash will always be trash.

295
00:16:34,431 --> 00:16:35,732
You think so?

296
00:16:40,537 --> 00:16:41,371
Well,

297
00:16:42,806 --> 00:16:43,640
I'll hold onto this.

298
00:16:45,075 --> 00:16:47,010
I'll get going soon.

299
00:16:48,445 --> 00:16:50,347
I'll keep practicing <i>Palxion</i>.

300
00:16:53,917 --> 00:16:55,085
Hey, Tomoki…

301
00:16:56,653 --> 00:16:58,222
-Is this--
-Hey, don't touch that!

302
00:16:58,288 --> 00:16:59,356
Sorry.

303
00:17:00,757 --> 00:17:02,059
Enough already.

304
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:04,127
-Just get out of here.
-Sorry.

305
00:17:04,194 --> 00:17:06,263
-Hurry.
-Sorry.

306
00:17:06,830 --> 00:17:07,831
See you again.

307
00:17:25,482 --> 00:17:27,417
YUKANAI

308
00:17:42,399 --> 00:17:43,534
I'm home.

309
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,935
I'm sorry I'm late.

310
00:17:45,002 --> 00:17:46,603
I'll get dinner ready right away.

311
00:18:02,085 --> 00:18:04,254
TATSUKI

312
00:18:05,589 --> 00:18:07,824
I WANT ANOTHER CHANCE
TO TALK WITH YOU AND SORA

313
00:18:07,891 --> 00:18:10,093
COULD YOU MAKE SOME TIME FOR ME?

314
00:18:20,437 --> 00:18:21,705
Hey there.

315
00:18:23,607 --> 00:18:25,375
Oh, everyone did junk art today?

316
00:18:25,442 --> 00:18:26,743
Yes.

317
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:27,744
I see.

318
00:18:27,811 --> 00:18:31,381
Did you make this, Mr. Tatsuki?

319
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:32,883
Yeah, but forget that.

320
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:34,251
‎Interesting…

321
00:18:35,118 --> 00:18:37,321
You're surprisingly romantic, huh?

322
00:18:37,988 --> 00:18:38,922
What do you mean?

323
00:18:39,790 --> 00:18:40,958
Who made this?

324
00:18:41,558 --> 00:18:42,726
Tomoki Yanagisawa.

325
00:18:43,794 --> 00:18:45,028
He hasn't been coming lately.

326
00:18:45,095 --> 00:18:48,232
Yeah, so we went
to visit him at his house,

327
00:18:48,298 --> 00:18:50,968
and made things together
using scraps in his room.

328
00:18:52,169 --> 00:18:53,103
You too, Shi-chan?

329
00:18:53,604 --> 00:18:56,306
I was kicked out.

330
00:18:57,474 --> 00:18:59,042
That's unfortunate.

331
00:19:00,110 --> 00:19:01,678
So he made a car, huh.

332
00:19:01,745 --> 00:19:03,480
Yes, he seems to like cars.

333
00:19:03,547 --> 00:19:06,216
But why did he

334
00:19:06,817 --> 00:19:08,752
attach dynamite to something he likes?

335
00:19:08,819 --> 00:19:11,288
Yeah, I wonder.

336
00:19:11,355 --> 00:19:14,725
And where is this headed?

337
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:20,530
Tomoki seemed like he was
a little on the edge.

338
00:19:21,365 --> 00:19:22,833
Is that right?

339
00:19:22,899 --> 00:19:26,503
While playing games,
he spoke pretty abrasively.

340
00:19:27,004 --> 00:19:30,607
But I was wondering if
that's how he's releasing his emotions.

341
00:19:30,674 --> 00:19:32,476
I see.

342
00:19:37,581 --> 00:19:40,050
TATSUKING

343
00:19:55,966 --> 00:19:58,302
I guess it's not that easy to find him.

344
00:20:06,109 --> 00:20:08,211
HARATOMO999 HAS INVITED YOU
TO JOIN HIS PARTY

345
00:20:08,812 --> 00:20:10,380
Oh, Tomoki!

346
00:20:12,449 --> 00:20:13,283
Okay.

347
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:14,618
YOU HAVE JOINED HARATOMO999'S PARTY

348
00:20:15,185 --> 00:20:16,453
All right.

349
00:20:18,822 --> 00:20:21,558
Tomoki, thanks for inviting me.

350
00:20:22,826 --> 00:20:25,662
This is a team battle,
so don't hold us back.

351
00:20:25,729 --> 00:20:27,831
No worries. You can count on me.

352
00:20:32,736 --> 00:20:33,570
Tatsuki.

353
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:40,677
Thanks to you,
I was able to kind of clear my head, and…

354
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,948
I was able to make up my mind.

355
00:20:47,117 --> 00:20:48,018
What do you mean?

356
00:20:49,152 --> 00:20:51,188
-Bye.
-What?

357
00:20:51,254 --> 00:20:52,422
Wait, Tomoki.

358
00:20:56,326 --> 00:20:57,861
Oh, crap.

359
00:20:59,863 --> 00:21:01,732
I wanted to talk to him a little more…

360
00:21:02,366 --> 00:21:03,233
Who are you?

361
00:21:03,734 --> 00:21:04,835
<i>I'm part of your team.</i>

362
00:21:06,169 --> 00:21:07,003
I'm sorry.

363
00:21:08,839 --> 00:21:09,673
<i>This way.</i>

364
00:21:14,878 --> 00:21:17,748
<i>I've never seen you before.</i>
<i>Are you friends with Haratomo?</i>

365
00:21:18,348 --> 00:21:19,182
Yes.

366
00:21:19,683 --> 00:21:20,650
We're buddies.

367
00:21:20,717 --> 00:21:25,322
<i>Then will you be joining the "festival"</i>
<i>on Friday too?</i>

368
00:21:26,289 --> 00:21:27,591
Festival?

369
00:21:28,091 --> 00:21:29,359
<i>Later.</i>

370
00:21:30,227 --> 00:21:31,995
Wait, what's this festival you mentioned?

371
00:21:36,633 --> 00:21:37,534
Festival?

372
00:21:39,803 --> 00:21:41,304
Friday…

373
00:21:41,371 --> 00:21:42,806
WEDNESDAY

374
00:22:01,558 --> 00:22:03,026
What's going on?

375
00:22:03,827 --> 00:22:04,661
Huh?

376
00:22:06,329 --> 00:22:07,664
I'm just cleaning up.

377
00:22:15,939 --> 00:22:18,542
OCTOBER 15TH THURSDAY

378
00:22:22,012 --> 00:22:23,880
Hello, this is Aomine at Yukanai.

379
00:22:28,585 --> 00:22:29,719
Is that right?

380
00:22:29,786 --> 00:22:31,988
Good morning, Mr. Tatsuki!

381
00:22:32,055 --> 00:22:34,558
Tomoki's grandmother just called.

382
00:22:34,624 --> 00:22:37,327
She said that Tomoki started
cleaning up his room.

383
00:22:37,394 --> 00:22:40,363
That's a good sign, isn't it?

384
00:22:40,864 --> 00:22:41,932
Give me five more minutes.

385
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,203
You're like a kid. Forget you.

386
00:23:01,518 --> 00:23:02,519
Oh, no.

387
00:23:04,254 --> 00:23:05,422
I'm sorry.

388
00:23:06,723 --> 00:23:08,191
How do I put this back?

389
00:23:35,452 --> 00:23:36,720
Mr. Tatsuki.

390
00:23:38,922 --> 00:23:41,691
Mr. Tatsuki, wake up!

391
00:23:44,394 --> 00:23:46,263
Wake up!

392
00:23:46,329 --> 00:23:47,497
What is it?

393
00:23:47,564 --> 00:23:51,601
Is this Tomoki?

394
00:23:52,802 --> 00:23:54,004
Yeah, what about it?

395
00:23:54,804 --> 00:23:55,739
I was

396
00:23:57,474 --> 00:24:00,010
his homeroom teacher.

397
00:24:00,911 --> 00:24:01,745
What?

398
00:24:05,181 --> 00:24:07,551
That's definitely you in this picture.

399
00:24:07,617 --> 00:24:11,054
His last name had changed
from Harada to Yanagisawa.

400
00:24:12,155 --> 00:24:14,024
So I didn't realize it was him.

401
00:24:15,859 --> 00:24:18,295
But if you were his homeroom teacher,

402
00:24:18,361 --> 00:24:19,996
did you know about the bullying?

403
00:24:20,830 --> 00:24:23,533
The thing is, I knew nothing about it.

404
00:24:24,301 --> 00:24:25,902
Even when he transferred schools,

405
00:24:25,969 --> 00:24:29,506
I was told that it was due
to his parents' work.

406
00:24:30,574 --> 00:24:32,509
They didn't tell the school about it?

407
00:24:33,343 --> 00:24:35,345
I had no idea

408
00:24:36,413 --> 00:24:38,748
there was bullying going on.

409
00:24:43,186 --> 00:24:44,821
Where did you find this picture?

410
00:24:46,022 --> 00:24:47,357
-In here.
-What?

411
00:24:47,424 --> 00:24:49,326
The picture was crumpled up

412
00:24:49,392 --> 00:24:51,728
and stuffed in here under the dynamite.

413
00:25:00,537 --> 00:25:01,938
<i>Thanks to you</i>

414
00:25:02,005 --> 00:25:04,407
I was able to kind of clear my head, and…

415
00:25:04,975 --> 00:25:06,409
I was able to make up my mind.

416
00:25:06,476 --> 00:25:10,180
<i>Then will you be joining the "festival"</i>
<i>on Friday too?</i>

417
00:25:11,881 --> 00:25:12,716
Ms. Shizuku.

418
00:25:13,783 --> 00:25:14,618
Yes?

419
00:25:15,452 --> 00:25:17,821
Friday might be some sort of a D-Day.

420
00:25:18,421 --> 00:25:19,522
D-Day?

421
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:27,764
MUSASHINO DAIHACHI MIDDLE SCHOOL

422
00:25:38,875 --> 00:25:39,943
RESIGNATION LETTER

423
00:25:40,010 --> 00:25:41,911
I don't have the confidence
to continue working here.

424
00:25:44,147 --> 00:25:46,950
I'm very sorry.

425
00:26:09,406 --> 00:26:11,441
Ms. Aomine?

426
00:26:12,842 --> 00:26:14,344
Long time no see.

427
00:26:16,613 --> 00:26:17,580
Um…

428
00:26:18,248 --> 00:26:21,017
I have some questions about Tomoki Harada.

429
00:26:21,084 --> 00:26:22,118
Can you girls help me out?

430
00:26:22,185 --> 00:26:24,287
What is it? What happened to Tomokin?

431
00:26:24,888 --> 00:26:26,656
During second grade…

432
00:26:27,323 --> 00:26:28,291
um…

433
00:26:29,492 --> 00:26:32,262
was there any bullying going on?

434
00:26:34,964 --> 00:26:38,068
Well, I guess you could call it bullying.

435
00:26:39,002 --> 00:26:40,804
Although I don't know much about it.

436
00:26:41,304 --> 00:26:43,940
It seems like he was being teased

437
00:26:44,007 --> 00:26:46,543
on social media and in group chats.

438
00:26:48,678 --> 00:26:50,113
By teasing, what do you mean?

439
00:26:51,014 --> 00:26:53,149
Remember how he was called Tomokin?

440
00:26:53,216 --> 00:26:54,284
‎Yeah.

441
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:56,252
But on social media,

442
00:26:56,319 --> 00:26:59,756
people were writing "kin" using
the character for "germs."

443
00:27:00,356 --> 00:27:01,391
Oh, right.

444
00:27:02,992 --> 00:27:04,994
I see.

445
00:27:05,895 --> 00:27:09,199
I had no idea that was going on.

446
00:27:09,265 --> 00:27:10,767
It's not your fault.

447
00:27:10,834 --> 00:27:14,704
It's impossible to check and keep up with
all the students' social media posts.

448
00:27:14,771 --> 00:27:16,439
Yeah, and things were normal during class.

449
00:27:18,341 --> 00:27:22,345
Do you happen to know who was
taking the lead in teasing him?

450
00:27:24,047 --> 00:27:25,849
I think it was Hiromu and his friends.

451
00:27:25,915 --> 00:27:27,517
Yeah, I think so too.

452
00:27:27,584 --> 00:27:29,052
Hiromu?

453
00:27:29,786 --> 00:27:31,821
Hiromu Hasegawa
in the track-and-field club?

454
00:27:31,888 --> 00:27:33,189
Yeah, him.

455
00:27:33,723 --> 00:27:35,125
Why do you want to know now?

456
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:39,529
I just wanted to be aware of it.

457
00:27:40,196 --> 00:27:41,030
Thank you.

458
00:27:42,332 --> 00:27:43,199
Bye.

459
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:44,934
Bye.

460
00:27:45,001 --> 00:27:46,169
Bye.

461
00:27:48,872 --> 00:27:52,742
<i>I did manage to get the name</i>
<i>of the student involved in the bullying.</i>

462
00:27:53,309 --> 00:27:56,246
But I haven't been able
to verify everything

463
00:27:56,312 --> 00:27:58,281
that I've heard so far.

464
00:27:59,048 --> 00:28:01,851
Then could it be that on D-Day,

465
00:28:01,918 --> 00:28:04,821
Tomoki is planning to take revenge
on those who bullied him?

466
00:28:04,888 --> 00:28:06,556
I was thinking the same thing.

467
00:28:09,192 --> 00:28:10,593
Tomorrow will mark

468
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:14,197
exactly one year
since Tomoki transferred schools.

469
00:28:15,265 --> 00:28:16,633
One year…

470
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,234
I have to end it.

471
00:28:20,904 --> 00:28:22,605
Since it'll be almost one year.

472
00:28:25,375 --> 00:28:28,178
He may indeed be planning something.

473
00:28:29,279 --> 00:28:30,280
Ms. Shizuku,

474
00:28:30,346 --> 00:28:33,049
maybe you can contact the student
who was bullying Tomoki.

475
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:34,784
Okay.

476
00:28:34,851 --> 00:28:38,354
I'll search for Tomoki on <i>Palxion</i>
until the very last moment.

477
00:28:39,989 --> 00:28:41,624
Wouldn't it be better to go to his house?

478
00:28:41,691 --> 00:28:42,892
No,

479
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:46,229
we can be more honest with each other
inside the game.

480
00:28:47,797 --> 00:28:49,599
I'll help you too.

481
00:28:50,266 --> 00:28:51,768
Yes.

482
00:28:51,835 --> 00:28:53,770
YUKANAI

483
00:28:53,837 --> 00:28:54,938
TATSUKING

484
00:28:56,139 --> 00:28:57,574
HARATOMO999 - OFFLINE

485
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,542
Tomoki is offline.

486
00:29:02,812 --> 00:29:05,248
Shall we take turns getting some sleep?

487
00:29:05,815 --> 00:29:09,886
Sure. This is kind of like a stakeout.

488
00:29:10,954 --> 00:29:13,256
-You can sleep first.
-No, you can go first.

489
00:29:13,923 --> 00:29:14,757
Leave it up to me.

490
00:29:18,094 --> 00:29:19,829
Okay, I'm counting on you.

491
00:29:20,330 --> 00:29:21,831
THURSDAY

492
00:29:29,205 --> 00:29:30,573
You're sleeping?

493
00:29:32,976 --> 00:29:34,077
TATSUKING

494
00:29:37,413 --> 00:29:38,448
Tomoki.

495
00:29:42,285 --> 00:29:43,753
I finally found you.

496
00:29:44,454 --> 00:29:45,889
I was looking for you.

497
00:29:47,357 --> 00:29:48,358
Why?

498
00:29:49,125 --> 00:29:50,460
What's the "festival"?

499
00:29:51,461 --> 00:29:52,328
‎Huh?

500
00:29:52,996 --> 00:29:55,598
You're planning
on doing something tomorrow, right?

501
00:29:57,267 --> 00:29:59,335
It's none of your business.

502
00:29:59,402 --> 00:30:02,071
I just got a bad feeling, that's all.

503
00:30:03,172 --> 00:30:04,974
It might be none of my business,

504
00:30:06,309 --> 00:30:07,810
but don't do anything dangerous.

505
00:30:10,046 --> 00:30:11,314
Tatsuki.

506
00:30:14,484 --> 00:30:15,518
Tatsuki,

507
00:30:16,819 --> 00:30:18,488
you're on my side, right?

508
00:30:19,289 --> 00:30:20,256
Of course.

509
00:30:20,323 --> 00:30:21,424
Then

510
00:30:22,191 --> 00:30:23,393
support me.

511
00:30:25,128 --> 00:30:28,264
That will depend on
what you're planning to do.

512
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:31,367
What a letdown.

513
00:30:33,603 --> 00:30:34,537
But

514
00:30:36,239 --> 00:30:37,407
I can say this for certain.

515
00:30:39,575 --> 00:30:41,144
If anything ever happens to you,

516
00:30:41,744 --> 00:30:42,612
I

517
00:30:43,813 --> 00:30:45,982
will risk my life
and definitely protect you.

518
00:30:47,984 --> 00:30:49,552
You're just an outsider.

519
00:30:51,688 --> 00:30:53,489
Stop spouting nonsense about how you'll

520
00:30:54,791 --> 00:30:56,893
-"definitely protect me."
-It's not a lie.

521
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,995
-I don't believe you.
-I'm being serious.

522
00:30:59,062 --> 00:31:00,496
Up until now,

523
00:31:01,431 --> 00:31:02,899
no matter what happened to me,

524
00:31:03,399 --> 00:31:06,102
there wasn't a single adult
who protected me.

525
00:31:08,237 --> 00:31:09,205
I've

526
00:31:11,007 --> 00:31:13,743
always been treated like trash.

527
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,654
I'm…

528
00:31:27,457 --> 00:31:29,425
definitely going to see it through.

529
00:31:31,794 --> 00:31:32,829
Tomoki.

530
00:31:40,269 --> 00:31:41,204
Tomoki.

531
00:31:46,542 --> 00:31:48,311
HARATOMO999
NO PLAYER BY THAT NAME EXISTS

532
00:31:49,212 --> 00:31:50,213
Tomoki.

533
00:31:51,614 --> 00:31:52,782
He disappeared.

534
00:31:56,019 --> 00:31:58,321
-"I'll definitely see it through"?
-Yes.

535
00:31:58,388 --> 00:32:00,556
What is he planning to do?

536
00:32:00,623 --> 00:32:04,594
I think it takes a lot of resolve
to delete your own account.

537
00:32:04,660 --> 00:32:06,662
-I bet.
-Yeah.

538
00:32:06,729 --> 00:32:08,831
How was he when he was making this?

539
00:32:11,267 --> 00:32:15,138
He said that the front of the car
looks like a face.

540
00:32:18,241 --> 00:32:21,044
Maybe he saw his own face in this artwork.

541
00:32:21,110 --> 00:32:23,212
His own face?

542
00:32:24,847 --> 00:32:26,649
Did you notice anything else?

543
00:32:27,417 --> 00:32:30,787
Did he seem scared, lonely, or sad?

544
00:32:32,088 --> 00:32:35,792
I couldn't pick up much, but he said…

545
00:32:35,858 --> 00:32:37,260
Up until now,

546
00:32:38,061 --> 00:32:39,462
no matter what happened to me,

547
00:32:39,529 --> 00:32:42,532
there wasn't a single adult
who protected me.

548
00:32:43,466 --> 00:32:45,902
It made me think
that he's harboring anger.

549
00:32:45,968 --> 00:32:48,137
-Anger?
-Yes.

550
00:32:50,673 --> 00:32:51,841
I see.

551
00:32:52,909 --> 00:32:55,111
What should we do?

552
00:33:05,521 --> 00:33:07,290
I think this flower that you made

553
00:33:07,356 --> 00:33:10,493
expresses your desire to protect.

554
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,561
Am I right?

555
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:20,803
You're the only one
who can protect Tomoki.

556
00:33:32,148 --> 00:33:34,283
YU

557
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:37,854
I CAN MAKE TIME TODAY
BETWEEN 17:00 TO 18:00

558
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,695
Today…

559
00:33:50,333 --> 00:33:52,268
-Bye.
-Bye.

560
00:33:52,335 --> 00:33:53,436
-Later.
-Bye.

561
00:33:53,503 --> 00:33:54,337
-Bye.
-Bye.

562
00:33:54,403 --> 00:33:56,606
You're Hiromu Hasegawa, right?

563
00:33:56,672 --> 00:33:58,407
MUSASHINO DAIHACHI MIDDLE SCHOOL

564
00:33:58,474 --> 00:34:00,343
Hey, Ms. Shizu!

565
00:34:00,409 --> 00:34:03,946
Sorry for stopping you like this.
Are you headed home now?

566
00:34:04,013 --> 00:34:05,648
What is it all of a sudden?

567
00:34:05,715 --> 00:34:08,918
You're not planning on meeting up
with anyone, are you?

568
00:34:08,985 --> 00:34:11,120
No, since there's a competition tomorrow.

569
00:34:11,187 --> 00:34:12,822
Oh, for track-and-field?

570
00:34:12,889 --> 00:34:16,259
My high school scholarship is on the line,
so I have to win this one.

571
00:34:16,325 --> 00:34:18,194
I see. Good luck.

572
00:34:18,961 --> 00:34:20,963
That's all. Sorry for bothering you.

573
00:34:22,365 --> 00:34:23,266
Bye.

574
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:25,535
Be careful.

575
00:34:47,823 --> 00:34:50,159
SORRY, I CAN'T MAKE IT JUST YET

576
00:35:10,446 --> 00:35:11,280
Hello?

577
00:35:11,347 --> 00:35:13,883
Hiromu made it home safely.

578
00:35:15,484 --> 00:35:17,486
No movements here either.

579
00:35:18,387 --> 00:35:21,057
<i>You can return to Yukanai for now.</i>

580
00:35:21,123 --> 00:35:22,258
Okay.

581
00:37:12,368 --> 00:37:13,669
What do you want?

582
00:37:15,504 --> 00:37:16,572
Oh, you caught me.

583
00:37:17,340 --> 00:37:18,441
You were so obvious.

584
00:37:19,975 --> 00:37:21,744
You're terrible at being inconspicuous,

585
00:37:21,811 --> 00:37:23,579
both in games and in real life.

586
00:37:24,914 --> 00:37:26,248
Seriously?

587
00:37:28,451 --> 00:37:29,685
Why did you follow me?

588
00:37:33,389 --> 00:37:34,423
Because

589
00:37:35,424 --> 00:37:37,360
I want to know
what the "festival" is about.

590
00:37:40,096 --> 00:37:41,330
Today marks one year

591
00:37:42,665 --> 00:37:44,333
since I transferred schools.

592
00:37:48,671 --> 00:37:49,605
Today

593
00:37:50,206 --> 00:37:52,775
is the anniversary of the day
I was driven out of school.

594
00:37:55,378 --> 00:37:56,278
I see.

595
00:38:03,552 --> 00:38:07,757
It all started with light teasing.

596
00:38:08,891 --> 00:38:11,026
<i>It didn't really bother me at first.</i>

597
00:38:12,094 --> 00:38:13,529
CLASS 2-3

598
00:38:13,596 --> 00:38:14,630
TOMOKIN SHOULD BE IN CHARGE
OF THE SHOPPING

599
00:38:14,697 --> 00:38:15,731
BUT HIS GERMS WILL SPREAD

600
00:38:15,798 --> 00:38:16,699
DON'T WANT HIS GERMS

601
00:38:16,766 --> 00:38:17,700
GO AWAY

602
00:38:17,767 --> 00:38:18,834
HE TOUCHED ME AND NOW THAT SPOT ITCHES

603
00:38:18,901 --> 00:38:19,969
HIS GERMS GOT TO YOU

604
00:38:27,643 --> 00:38:29,011
WHAT? TOMOKIN IS STILL IN THIS CHAT?

605
00:38:29,078 --> 00:38:30,846
SERIOUSLY?

606
00:38:30,913 --> 00:38:32,314
GROSS, I CAN'T STAND HIM

607
00:38:32,381 --> 00:38:33,482
HIS GERMS WILL GET TO ME

608
00:38:36,619 --> 00:38:37,887
HASEGAWA HAS LEFT THE GROUP CHAT

609
00:38:37,953 --> 00:38:39,922
HARU HAS LEFT THE GROUP CHAT

610
00:38:55,271 --> 00:38:59,074
The instigator was a guy named Hiromu.

611
00:39:00,309 --> 00:39:01,744
From track-and-field?

612
00:39:01,811 --> 00:39:03,746
So you know, huh?

613
00:39:05,448 --> 00:39:07,850
The truth is, I want to knock him down.

614
00:39:09,084 --> 00:39:11,020
But I don't have the strength to do that.

615
00:39:14,089 --> 00:39:15,257
Apparently,

616
00:39:16,025 --> 00:39:19,161
he's going to high school
on a sports scholarship.

617
00:39:20,796 --> 00:39:22,431
Isn't it unfair?

618
00:39:23,132 --> 00:39:25,000
When he made me suffer this much.

619
00:39:26,936 --> 00:39:27,937
You're right.

620
00:39:28,003 --> 00:39:29,305
So,

621
00:39:30,506 --> 00:39:33,609
I decided to expose
all the evidence of his bullying online.

622
00:39:35,811 --> 00:39:39,548
Then he won't get his scholarship.

623
00:39:42,551 --> 00:39:46,021
Is that what the "festival" is about?

624
00:39:49,492 --> 00:39:51,026
That's not all.

625
00:40:00,236 --> 00:40:02,571
Oh, you surprised me.

626
00:40:02,638 --> 00:40:05,307
-Iino, is that you?
-Sorry for scaring you.

627
00:40:06,008 --> 00:40:07,009
Ms. Shizuku.

628
00:40:08,010 --> 00:40:10,479
-Funamori?
-Please save Tomoki.

629
00:40:10,546 --> 00:40:11,914
‎What?

630
00:40:19,989 --> 00:40:20,956
I'm

631
00:40:22,391 --> 00:40:23,759
going to end my life here.

632
00:40:24,894 --> 00:40:25,895
‎What?

633
00:40:25,961 --> 00:40:28,931
I entrusted all the evidence
to my friends.

634
00:40:28,998 --> 00:40:31,467
I told them to expose everything
once I'm dead.

635
00:40:32,201 --> 00:40:33,502
Then

636
00:40:34,937 --> 00:40:36,805
he'll die too, socially.

637
00:40:39,909 --> 00:40:41,744
I think that'll be good enough.

638
00:40:44,146 --> 00:40:46,582
I tell all the kids who come to Yukanai

639
00:40:48,317 --> 00:40:49,852
that they can be free

640
00:40:50,452 --> 00:40:52,321
and do whatever they want.

641
00:40:54,456 --> 00:40:55,491
But

642
00:40:55,558 --> 00:40:57,927
I say that in order
to keep everyone safe and protected.

643
00:41:00,029 --> 00:41:01,297
And right now,

644
00:41:02,731 --> 00:41:04,600
I have to protect you.

645
00:41:07,603 --> 00:41:08,904
I won't let you kill yourself.

646
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:12,074
It's

647
00:41:13,208 --> 00:41:14,977
-already game over for me.
-Tomoki.

648
00:41:15,044 --> 00:41:17,112
I don't like dragging things out

649
00:41:18,814 --> 00:41:20,749
when I know that I've already

650
00:41:20,816 --> 00:41:22,451
-lost.
-But you still can't die!

651
00:41:22,518 --> 00:41:24,987
You say that,

652
00:41:25,654 --> 00:41:27,923
but I'm the one who has to keep living.

653
00:41:29,525 --> 00:41:31,627
Stop saying, "Don't die,"
when you can't take

654
00:41:32,261 --> 00:41:33,696
responsibility for it.

655
00:41:35,130 --> 00:41:38,133
You've probably never considered
the feelings of someone

656
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,635
who's wanting to die.

657
00:41:39,702 --> 00:41:41,303
I have, that's why I'm saying this!

658
00:41:46,875 --> 00:41:48,177
Remember

659
00:41:49,645 --> 00:41:51,413
how I told you about the kid

660
00:41:52,214 --> 00:41:54,183
who refused to go to school,
and I screwed up

661
00:41:55,017 --> 00:41:56,852
by forcing him out of his room?

662
00:41:58,921 --> 00:42:00,122
That…

663
00:42:03,325 --> 00:42:04,860
That was about my son.

664
00:42:08,297 --> 00:42:09,999
Later on,

665
00:42:11,667 --> 00:42:13,902
<i>he attempted suicide.</i>

666
00:42:20,242 --> 00:42:21,877
I never

667
00:42:24,713 --> 00:42:27,650
want to repeat that same mistake again.

668
00:42:30,886 --> 00:42:32,321
So

669
00:42:34,923 --> 00:42:38,027
I swore that I would protect everyone
no matter what.

670
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:43,132
What's that got to do with me?

671
00:42:44,967 --> 00:42:46,468
Stop pushing

672
00:42:47,136 --> 00:42:49,138
-your dreams and ideals on me.
-Tomoki.

673
00:42:49,204 --> 00:42:52,307
Trash will always be trash.

674
00:42:53,275 --> 00:42:55,678
-It will forever be trash.
-You're not trash.

675
00:42:57,446 --> 00:42:58,881
You're not trash.

676
00:43:10,693 --> 00:43:12,127
Let's go back.

677
00:43:16,365 --> 00:43:17,833
Let's go back,

678
00:43:19,234 --> 00:43:21,170
and continue playing that game.

679
00:43:41,990 --> 00:43:42,991
Bye.

680
00:43:48,764 --> 00:43:49,998
Tomoki!

681
00:43:57,706 --> 00:43:58,741
Tatsuki.

682
00:44:01,076 --> 00:44:02,077
Tatsuki!

683
00:44:06,782 --> 00:44:09,518
Tatsuki.

684
00:44:10,786 --> 00:44:12,654
What should I do? Tatsuki!

685
00:44:16,191 --> 00:44:17,192
Tomoki.

686
00:44:17,259 --> 00:44:18,260
Tatsuki.

687
00:44:19,762 --> 00:44:20,596
Answer that.

688
00:44:22,164 --> 00:44:23,332
SHIZUKU AOMINE

689
00:44:25,033 --> 00:44:26,568
Hello?

690
00:44:26,635 --> 00:44:30,405
-<i>Mr. Tatsuki?</i>
-What should I do? Tatsuki is…

691
00:44:30,472 --> 00:44:32,141
Tatsuki is…

692
00:44:32,207 --> 00:44:34,343
Tomoki? Hello?

693
00:44:34,409 --> 00:44:35,911
What about Mr. Tatsuki?

694
00:44:36,545 --> 00:44:37,379
He's bleeding

695
00:44:38,247 --> 00:44:39,081
from his arm…

696
00:44:39,148 --> 00:44:40,249
<i>He's bleeding.</i>

697
00:44:40,883 --> 00:44:43,218
Tomoki, pull yourself together.
Is anyone else there?

698
00:44:43,285 --> 00:44:45,354
No. What am I supposed to do?

699
00:44:45,420 --> 00:44:47,022
Stop the bleeding immediately!

700
00:44:47,089 --> 00:44:48,857
<i>-Can you do it?</i>
-No, I can't.

701
00:44:48,924 --> 00:44:50,325
<i>Tomoki, you can do it.</i>

702
00:44:50,392 --> 00:44:52,494
<i>Apply strong pressure to the wound.</i>

703
00:44:58,033 --> 00:44:58,901
Don't die.

704
00:44:59,568 --> 00:45:01,503
Don't die, Tatsuki.

705
00:45:06,275 --> 00:45:09,244
I had become a useless adult.

706
00:45:09,311 --> 00:45:10,279
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

707
00:45:10,345 --> 00:45:11,213
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

708
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:12,247
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita

